<br>
Intellect and wisdom are both only tools, and we need both to help us make choices. The poem isn't about slipping blandly away into a sea nothingness, it's about not making up your mind about things and dividing them and sticking-them-put in such a way that you can't ever let them move from the spots you've decided they will always occupy. Once you've determined that you already know all the ways you'll ever need to learn, you've pretty much cut yourself off.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately, fanatacism is all about having already decided how you're going to judge the world, and there are far too many fanatics already trying to shape the world in a way that would prove that they are right. That's why I don't believe in running around trying to give answers. Not only do I think it doesn't do any good when other ears just won't hear them, I also personally learn a lot more from focussing on the questions themselves rather than trying too hard to be &quot;right&quot; with my answers. And when I make a choice, I take personal responsibility for it rather than blaming it on a god.<br>
<br>
But I'm used to being called silly and not making any sense, so I'll go have that nap! Just please, don't put any more words in my mouth while I'm sleeping! It'll make me snore...<br>
<br>
