But sorry, I am unable to do that now.<br>
Next time, maybe.... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
And Kimaya, when I read this poem I feel nothingness.<br>
What you feel reading it is different than what I feel... but that can happen sometimes, it is not a big matter.<br>
I also think a lot on questions themselves. But questions want an answer, otherwise they aren't real questions. Those I think I can answer I will try to answer, and still confess openly that maybe my answer is wrong. Those I think I cannot answer, I'll say I cannot answer. Those I think they are useless I'll say they are useless questions. Sometimes I may be wrong, sometimes I may be right, it is up to the listener to determine that and find his own way. It is as simple.<br>
And, I don't know anything, actually! Life is permanent learning. But we have to act to be able to learn. And to ask questions, and to try to find answers. That's my humble opinion.<br>
