The discussion about good/neutral/evil will never have an end. This thread wasn't the first one, and won't be the last one. It is a difficult question, but I try to make some things clear.<br>
The answer will depend on the character's basic beliefs. And there are in my opinion 2 basic approaches:<br>
1) Those who use evil/neutral/good to establish a division, for example a high elf paladin who thinks all dark elves and iksar as evil, while paladins are good, druids are neutral, and so on. Or like Zildrax who thinks he is good, and all 'softskins' are evil, or at least should be conquered and killed/enslaved.<br>
2) Those who don't care about the division, and play evil paladins, good necromancers, or iksar who like to help high elves or whatsoever. Or those who don't play them, but at least interact with them (for example a paladin who groups with a 'good' necromancer, or a shadowknight grouping with a 'evil paladin').<br>
Well, and those above are the roleplayers. Unfortunately there are also some non-roleplayers who don't care at all about anything. But that's a different question.<br>
<br>
So some people use evil/good as general label put on a race/class to define borders and enemies. Others see every single person separately, as evil or good, according to his/her actions.<br>
Nobody is right, nobody is wrong, all are great roleplayers, and we all try our best to have great fun together.<br>
<br>
